A few film and digital shots from our in-home photo shoot back in September 🥹 Planned shoots in a pretty location are great and all but these ones at home, they are extra special 🤎

Also that leg in photo 5 😂

William got an upgrade 🥰

It took 6 months, but I finally found the crib of my dreams! Shopping second hand takes time but it’s so rewarding. We spent a grand total of $10 after we sold the old one!

Our breastfeeding journey has been strong from the very beginning. I was nervous with him born premature and in the NICU for 6 days, that breastfeeding would be a challenge. But it came more naturally this time than the others, all glory to GOD! And now, 1.5 years later, we still share that bond. My others were nearly weaned by this age but we are nowhere near weaning this time. I’m not sure when he’ll be ready. But until then, I will soak up these remaining moments with him 🤎

Our newest kitchen DIY! 🔨 

Our kitchen has come a looooong way in the last year (swipe 👉🏻 to see). I love being able to transform this home into ‘us’. And I’m so grateful for all the hard work and love my husband has poured into these projects 🥰

2022 included more hospital visits, ambulance rides, and sickness than I’ve ever experienced in my life. But with the trials brought deep growth, peace, and understanding that only the Lord could provide. All glory and honor to HIM 🌟

Also the CHANGES that happened in our home this year was 🔥 

Farewell 2022 👋🏻

One year in the making and it was TOTALLY worth the wait 😍 

Head over to www.delilahloeppky.com (linked in my bio) to explore my new website! Huge thanks to my brother, @liam_wiebe_design for making my dreams come to life, and to @doxa.photography for taking stunning photos of our family to showcase here.

Get excited for newsletters to restart and *hopefully* the odd blog post (aka recipes!!). This is also the place to come if you are looking for links of any kind - go to ‘shop’ in the drop down menu and explore! 

And hey, now that this project is complete, maybe I’ll finally get around to launching my newest presets 😅

Two marriage goals for 2023
1. Kiss more
2. Date more

For our sake and our children’s sake we want to make our marriage top priority - and to show our affection in front of our kids! Compliment one another, hug, kiss, hold hands, flirt, giggle. Our arms may be full with little ones but there should always be room left for one another. No excuses 😘

📸 @doxa.photography

I loved decorating this nursery for our little man this past year. It’s one of my favorite rooms in the house - so calming and serene. But once he *finally* starts sleeping through the night we’ll be moving him in with Theo and this room will be Eloise’s. I’m already dreaming up all the fun room designs 😍 I’m thinking 🦕 🦖 wallpaper in the boys room for sure and a splash of pink on the walls for miss Eloise! It’ll be fun to step out of the box a little and play around with their favorite things! But I better start planning now so I have time to make up my mind 😅

Admittedly I’m very picky about the clothes I allow into my closet. Happy birthday to the one who put up with my weird, annoying texts a decade ago 🤪

To the one who happily carries the load, who guides and protects, who loves when we’re not so loveable, we love you so much. Happy birthday 🥳 

And enjoy these forgotten photos from summer, because apparently I don’t take any photos in winter 😅

What do you do with all the photos collected over the years? I physically print film photos and stick them in an album and it’s so much fun to flip through. But all the tens of thousands of digital photos piled up on my phone and computer just sit there, unseen. I’m thinking about making it a tradition to print a photo book for each child for their birthday of their last year, so they can keep photos of themselves and see how much they’ve grown over the years. And I’d love to print a few of these ☝🏻 treasured family photos to frame around the house 🥰

All colors were color matched at a local hardware store!

Swiss Coffe by Benjamin Moore - the most beautiful creamy white! Used on our ceilings, trims, and on the walls throughout the living room, kitchen, play room, entrance, and hall.

Crisp Linen by Behr - a warm, cozy greige. Used on the walls in all of our bedrooms - a safe option until we re-do the rooms!

Florentine Plaster by Benjamin Moore - a medium, creamy green-grey that adds a lovely contrast in our home! Used on all of the doors and the kids wardrobe.

French Canvas by Benjamin Moore - a stunning, soft light green. Used on the shiplap in our en-suite.

Heather by Dunn Edwards - the perfect beige. Used on our kitchen cabinets!
Praising the Lord for this tiny miracle 🤎

THANK YOU for your sweet well wishes and congratulations ☺️ I cannot believe this is the forth baby I’ve carried in my womb and I feel blessed beyond measure!

I know it’s not easy for some to see pregnancy announcements. Many are navigating their way through painful loss and miscarriage, infertility, and heartache. I see your pain and my heart and prayer goes out to all of you. If you need to hit that unfollow button for a while, don’t hesitate to do so. Joy can coexist with grief but sometimes it’s necessary to step away and just take care of yourself too 🤎

Life is happening at the speed of lightening these days and then I realize I haven’t posted anything in over a week 🙃 It’s funny because 3 years ago I would excitedly post 1-2 times a DaY and now I can’t even remember to take a photo. My arms are fuller now and so is my heart 🤎

But hey, here’s me, 13 weeks pregnant with little love #4 🥰 I’m trying to stay on top of documenting the belly in photos and now that my energy is slowly returning hopefully I can be more present here! What kind of pregnancy-related content are you most eager to see??

My Valentine’s 🤎

🎞 by @doxa.photography

It’s wild to think that soon this nursery will no longer be William’s room 🥺 Also still trying to wrap my head around the fact that there is a baby inside my womb right now. It doesn’t really feel real until I am consistently feeling those punches and jabs from within. What week did you first start feeling those movements?

Popping this in your feed to remind you (and myself) that winter won’t last forever 😅

Photos by the ever-talented @doxa.photography

At 15 weeks baby is the size of a 🍐 Tiny taste buds have formed and facial expressions are developing. They are beginning to practice breathing and sucking motions now and are likely already sucking their tiny thumb 🥹

( ….yes, this is posted nearly 2 weeks late but that’s what happens when your arms and days are full with 3 other kiddos 🤪)

Mamas: what transition was easiest for you? For me 0-1 was the hardest by far, 1-2 the easiest, and 2-3 was somewhere in between. Now I’m sitting here wondering how on earth we’re going to manage 3-4 but also so excited for it all 🤎 

The biggest thing I’ve noticed with each transition is the farther I let myself slip from the Lord, the harder it is. So I’m working on consistent habits of praying throughout the day, spending some time in His word, listening to the Bible & biblical podcasts when I can, and shifting my mindset from a “me” perspective to one that serves with a heart of gratitude. 👈🏻 That last one is game-changing, let me tell you! In all the excitement and preparation for a new baby, don’t forget to prepare your heart and soul too 🙏🏻

8 years, 5 pregnancies 👧🏼👼🏻👦🏻👶🏼🤰

👧🏼 November 2016 - July 2017
👼🏻 July 2018 
👦🏻 August 2018 - April 2019
👶🏼 November 2020 - June 2021 
🤰 December 2022 - August 2023

There once was a time when I got irritated when my children woke up early and my “me-time” was interrupted too soon. But this mindset shift changed everything 👉🏻

Instead of complaining that I never got time alone, I realized this was a perfect opportunity to invite them into my quiet time and show them what that looks like. This is mommy’s way of preparing her home and heart for the day ahead.

What I once found annoying I now find endearing, watching them eagerly help me make coffee and empty the dishwasher and read books while I read my Bible. Those early mornings are not as quiet and relaxing as they are when I get the chance to be alone, but those sweet moments are ones that will become fond memories I cherish and hold dear when they are raising families of their own 🤎

20 weeks ✨

It’s funny how the first half of pregnancy doesn’t really feel real and then suddenly it hits … we’re already halfway there and there’s an actual human inside of me 🤯 Today marks the halfway point of this pregnancy and we are growing more and more excited to know who this missing piece of our puzzle is! One thing is for sure, he or she is already so very deeply loved 🤎

Outfit of the day, #bumpedition

Links to everything can be found at https://liketk.it/45Uvv (linked in my stories!)

Thank you all for the well wishes and encouragement on the last vlog. Honestly I was feeling really gutted that day but my heart has been filled with peace since then and I know we rest in the good Lord’s hands. As much as I deeply long for a redemptive, peaceful, hands-off birth, I will do whatever it takes to get our sweet babe earth-side and safe and sound. We are so grateful baby is healthy and I plan to soak in every minute and movement with him or her in my womb 🤎 

The next ultrasound is booked and in the meantime we are praying, praying, praying! 🙏🏻
This weather is everything ☀️ and my man is 🔥🥵

Officially in the third trimester and things are really starting to feel real 😳 Y’all we’re having a baby soon………..

Mother’s Day recap 🌸

Breakfast in bed (for the first time ever!), church, picnic lunch, green house shopping, and charcuterie dinner in celebration of my Mama’s birthday 💐
Garden planting season 🌱

Someone got a little more freedom 👀 We took the rail off his bed last week and it’s been a surprisingly smooth adjustment so far! Now to transition him into the big kids room … that might be a bigger adventure 😅

Slowly we are starting to prepare for baby #4! And that includes a lot of changes for this guy. We’re taking it one step at a time as to *hopefully* not overwhelm him too much. But then again, maybe going cold turkey would be better? Would did you do with your youngest ones in preparation for a new sibling?

8 years, 1 van, and nearly 4 kids later 😍

First photo was taken on our recent vacation, second photo was taken on our Honeymoon (when we were 19 and too young to rent a vehicle but we could rent a u-haul 😂)

If you missed the vacation vlog head over to my channel to catch up!
28 weeks pregnant and my “before baby to do list” is growing longer by the second 😳 Nesting mode will be in FULL FORCE from now until the day this baby makes his/her arrival 🧺

This has to be one of my most favorite photos ever. The feeing of warmth and joy and gratitude attached to this memory is one I will never forget 🌸

Also, whatever this bush is, I want one in my backyard 😍

I cannot thank you all enough for your kindness and encouragement and prayers. I was nervous to post my pregnancy update. I even had Zach watch the video first, in fear that I was being irrational and overly emotional. But you all blew me away with the amount of support and PRAYER. I’m in tears knowing how covered we are in prayer right now. That very day my heart was filled with more peace than I ever thought possible. I had resigned myself to the reality of another c-section but that day I felt HOPE that maybe we’ll get the birth I’ve been dreaming of after all. Regardless of what happens, God is GOOD and there is power in prayer 👊🏻

Let’s talk BABY NAMES!
We are sTruGgliNg this time around with both boy and girl names. We have a couple we like but nothing solid yet. Help a girl out and share some suggestions in the comments, please 😅
Scenes from last September, captured by the talented @doxa.photography 📸 How fun will it be to recapture these moments with a SIXTH member of the family in a couple short months!? 🤎

Are you walking through a season of change and growth? I’m right here with you 🙋🏻‍♀️

It’s not an easy road, especially when your plans and dreams are turned upside down. But it is in seasons like these that I learn to surrender. I wish I could describe to you the peace that comes with fully surrendering everything to our Creator. Because of HIM I can smile in the storm. And when I come through to the other side I always look back and marvel at how good our God is and praise Him for continuing the good work He began in me!
A little birthday recap 🎈

Acknowledging the discomfort and pain is okay and important! But let us not allow our hearts to stay there. Giving thanks even in the hardships changed me from the inside out and I am so much more full of joy because of it!

Count it all joy my friends 💐

To the one who daily lays down his life to serve, love, and lead our family,

We love you so much 🫶🏻

Happy Father’s Day!

We are weeks away from having this baby and our home is turned upside down in preparation 🙈 Our bedroom is being renovated, our basement is in the midst of a purge, and the rest of our home has been disregarded in the middle of it all. It is chaos 😅 I’m losing steam much faster these days as my body prepares to give birth and our hearts are growing more and more excited to hold this miracle in our arms. These last days of pregnancy are wild and sweet. I’m soaking in every moment of it all 🤎

What was your child’s reaction to a new sibling? Was it exactly as you expected or completely different? I’m so curious how the reactions will be to baby #4. Lately they’ve all been really into playing dolls and practicing changing diapers and taking their babies for walks and it’s so sweet 🥹
Only 8 more to go (but probably less 🙊)

It’s baby month!!! 

(Most likely).

My due date is in August BUT that placenta just wants to keep hanging out down low so unless it miraculously moves in the next few weeks, this baby is coming THIS MONTH! 

These two will both be July babies 🥹

We have officially hit the uncomfortable stage of pregnancy 😅 I’ve noticed a lot of shifts in my body recently and I know it is preparing to bring this baby into the world. So soon little one, so soon 🤎 

P.S. my newsletter goes out in a couple hours and this is one you do not want to miss!! It may include a sneak peek of our bedroom makeover AND the much-anticipated sourdough sandwich loaf recipe you all have been waiting for! 🍞 Just go to the link in my bio, scroll to the bottom of my website, and enter your email under “subscribe to my newsletter”!
Maternity photo sneak peeks!!! @doxa.photography outdoes herself every time 😍
Okay baby, we’re ready for you 🤎

We are in the home stretch now. I’ve been pondering how I want to spend these last days, and I want to spend them exactly like this.

Slow, intentional.

There are tasks I’d like to accomplish yet before this babe arrives but I do not want to let these moments pass me by. 
-
If you are looking for a fun summer family activity, try berry picking! Our tree didn’t produce more than a single bowl this year so we headed to a local u-pick and we all had a blast!

THE PLACENTA IS MOVING!!!

Against all odds, the placenta moved 11mm at the last ultrasound! This opens up the possibility of going for a trial of labor, which has been my hope and prayer all along! This week we will check one final time to see where things are at and create a birth plan accordingly. If the placenta moves 1 more cm we will be free of all of this 🙏🏻

We are praising God and rejoicing at this miraculous and unexpected turn of events! 

God is good. 

Psalm 40:5
Many, Lord my God, are the wonders you have done, the things you planned for us. None can compare with you; were I to speak and tell of your deeds, they would be too many to declare.

Yesterday’s ultrasound appointment left us with more questions than answers. I was hoping to have a solid birth plan in place but instead we are confused and waiting and hoping to see our doctor one last time. 

Surrender. Surrender. Surrender. 

For now I’m enjoying every painful kick from within and praising God for each day this baby stays safe inside my womb. Every day they stay in there is *hopefully* one less day in the NICU!

Watching, waiting, hoping, praying, carrying two heartbeats in one body 🤎

And this hymn we sung in church on Sunday hit home in a whole new way.

Dear Baby,

Today was supposed to be your birthday. We saw you yesterday and, by the grace of God, it looks like you get a little more time to cook. You might be an August baby after all! We are grateful for the extra time you have in there. Get those lungs good and strong so when we finally meet you you can stay in our arms, okay? We love you so much already. 

Love, Mama, Dad, and your very excited siblings ❤️

Snapshots from the last few days 📸

Watching, waiting, praying, trusting.
Filling my mind with scripture that assures of His great love and strength 🤎
Rewinding time for a sec to reminisce on this sweet trip. How fun it will be to travel with FOUR in the backseat soon!

Ever since this years curriculum arrived the kids have been begging to start up school once again. This week we *very causally* spent a couple rainy mornings dipping our toes back into the water and it has been so lovely! We’re taking a more hands on, laid back approach this year and we are so excited to watch the learning unfold!

Snippets of the last few weeks as we wait. We can’t be far from a hospital and Zach and I need to be glued at the hip right now in case anything happens. So we’ve been enjoying slower paced days together going for many walks and swims, eating lots of ice cream, putting a pause on bigger projects and busying ourselves with small ones instead. Trying to keep busy and distracted while also ready to make a break for the hospital at any time is a balancing act and we are all-too-eager to just meet this little one already!
Any time now baby 🧺
Happy due date 🤍

Want to hear something strange?

3 times last weekend a stranger observed our family, came up to us, and called us blessed. 3 times. Never, and I mean NEVER has someone said that to us before. We get side glances and comments like, “You have your hands full!” or “You must be busy!” all the time, but never has someone said we were blessed to have a quiver full of children. It was like God was reminding us that children are a BLESSING, not a burden. It was so cool.
Our bodies are amazing 🥺
Nearly 1 month already 😭

Soothing their sister to sleep with the new @lovevery Music Set ❤️ When toys are suitable for a wide range of ages and encourage my children to learn, explore, and play together … I mean, what more could I ask for?? Zach and I have already been the audience to many performances and Annie has been lovingly serenaded countless times. It is so sweet watching their friendship grow 🎼 #loveverymelody

Someone asked me recently if I’ve had a moment of doubt since Annie joined the family, a moment where I thought maybe this is too much.

Honestly? This has been the most natural transition yet. There are times when it feels overwhelming but never has there been a moment of doubt. She was the missing piece to our family puzzle 🌻

Happy 8 years Honey 😘

In this season of motherhood I often feel I’m falling short. Too often I listen to the enemy’s voice saying, “You’re not good enough.”

It is in those moments I need to remind myself where my worth is found. My worth is not found in how many activities I do with my children or how clean my house is or how much I accomplished that day. My worth is found in CHRIST. 

When I believe that truth I can shush the enemy’s lies and live a life that is full and joyful. I may not be able to do all that I would like to right now. Instead, I can be slow and intentional with my time and energy, using it to glorify the Lord who made me. 

I don’t have to pretend like I have it all together. I don’t have to be more or do more.

I am enough.
What a beautiful life it is 🌟

And I wouldn’t have it any other way 🤍
